%div.info#photo_faq
  %div.intro.span16
    %h3 Administrator FAQ
    %p This FAQ section helps Site Administrator's to configure site settings.

  %div.span16
    %div.well.expandable.collapsed{:style => "width:865px;"}
      %h4 1. How to configure Facebook App in our Application?
      = link_to "read more...", "#",:class=>"read-more"
      %div.inner{:style => "display: none;"}
        %p 
          1. Login to 
          %i https://developers.facebook.com
        %p 2. Go to Tools Page by clicking the Tools menu in the top bar.
        %p 3. Click 'App Dashboard' in the left sidebar or  'App Dashboard' link under 'Creating, managing and testing your App' area.
        %p 4. It leads you to Facebook App development page.
        %p 5. Click 'Create new App' button in top right.
        %p 6. 'Create New App' popup will appear, enter a valid App Name( this one should be your Display name) and continue.
        %p 7. A 'Security Check Required' box will appear, enter the given captcha in the text field and submit.
        %p 8. Now you are in App's Basic settings page.
        %p 9. Enter your domain address in 'App Domains' area.
        %p 10. Enter the category and sub category things, it's an optional one.
        %p 11. Check the 'Website with Facebook Login' link and enter you site url there( if your application supports Facebook login)
        %p 12. Copy your 'App ID' and 'App Secret' from the top.
        %p 13. Save your changes.
        %p 14. Login to application's admin console.
        %p 15. Go to settings/config menu.
        %p 16. Paste the Facebook App ID and Secret in the desired fields in the 'Credentials for external services' area.
        %p 17. Save your changes.
          
    %div.well.expandable.collapsed{:style => "width:865px;"}
      %h4 2. How to configure Twitter App in our Application ?
      = link_to "read more...", "#",:class=>"read-more"
      %div.inner{:style => "display: none;"}
        %p 
          1. Login to 
          %i https://dev.twitter.com
        %p 2. Click 'Create an app' and this leads you to the app settings page .
        %p 3. Enter your application name, description, website and callback url, agree the terms and conditions, enter captacha text and click 'Create your Twitter Application'.
        %p 4. Now you are in your twitter app settings page.
        %p 5. Click 'create my access token' button in the details tab
        %p 6. Go to settings tab.
        %p 7. Select your application icon.
        %p 8. Change Application Type access, now it's in read access, change that to 'Read, Write and Access direct messages'.
        %p 9. Save your changes by clicking 'Update this Twitter Applications Settings'.
        %p 10. Go to OAuth tool tab and copy the Consumer key and Consumer secret.
        %p 11. Login to application's admin console.
        %p 12. Go to settings/config menu.
        %p 13. Paste 'Consumer key' to 'Twitter App Id' and 'Consumer secret' to 'Twitter Secret' in the 'Credentials for external services' area.
        %p 14. Save your changes.
          
%script
  Expandable.initialize("#photo_faq");